OUTTAKES: LYNCH MOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Leonard Klady 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An iconoclastic director like David Lynch -- of "Eraserhead," and "Blue Velvet" 
fame -- working in network TV? Come on! 
</P>
<P>
But sources tell us that Lynch will start a pilot movie for a mystery-thriller 
series, "Northwest Passage," in Seattle, come March, for ABC. Kyle MacLachlin 
stars as an FBI agent investigating the murder of a high school homecoming 
queen. Also cast: Isabella Rossellini and Harry Dean Stanton. 
</P>
<P>
The movie was written by Lynch and Mark Forest and is set in a small Peyton 
Place-type community populated by unusual characters -- such as a deputy 
sheriff who breaks into tears whenever he's faced with an emotional situation. 
</P>
<P>
According to a source close to the production, "Melodrama is too tame a word to 
describe the emotional tone. Every aspect of story and style have been 
heightened." 
</P>
<P>
David Latt produces with Propaganda Films. Leonard Klady 
</P>
