<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN ON THE JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
What your article on women who are "making it" shows is that the companies for 
which these women work are gender-blind only if their employees are not 
mothers. Maybe this is because you'd have had to devote at least 10 times the 
space to women who, by your standards, are not making it because the men and 
childless and/or affluent women in management can't relate to parental 
responsibilities and refuse to allow parents to successfully combine work and 
parenthood. 
</P>
<P>
KRISTIN BLANCHARD 
</P>
<P>
West Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
