</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROCKIN' AND RACKIN' THE CRITIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Will someone please inform Robert Hilburn that his feeble attempt at being the 
weatherman of rock 'n' roll is not amusing ("Today's Stars: Tomorrow's 
Legends," Jan. 15). 
</P>
<P>
According to Hilburn, at the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame there is a 60% chance 
of scattered Los Lobos, followed by a 35% chance of Billy Idol. The high will 
be 99% Michael Jackson and the low will be 1% Tiffany. 
</P>
<P>
Tell us, Mr. Hilburn, should we take our umbrella? 
</P>
<P>
RICK STEPHENSON 
</P>
<P>
West Covina 
</P>
</TEXT>
