<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON ART MUSEUM FUNDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re: "Architectural Design on a User-Friendly Scale," Jan. 10. 
</P>
<P>
It came as quite a surprise to read in Leon Whiteson's otherwise informative 
review of an exhibition at the Gallery of Functional Art that the Santa Monica 
Museum of Art is a "privately funded" institution. Quite the contrary. 
</P>
<P>
The museum is a nonprofit, tax-exempt organization dependent upon public 
support. We are wholly supported by contributions from our membership and board 
of trustees, and through grants from governmental agencies, corporations and 
charitable foundations. A great many individuals have generously lent their 
time, expertise and money to making the museum a reality. It is this collective 
effort and public good will that supports the Santa Monica Museum of Art. 
</P>
<P>
THOMAS RHOADS 
</P>
<P>
Director 
</P>
<P>
Santa Monica Museum of Art 
</P>
</TEXT>
