<TEXT>
<P>
Despite attempts by Syria and Iran to stop the violence, two bombs exploded in 
Lebanon, resulting in at least one death. Police said one person was killed and 
11 were injured, including a Syrian soldier, when a car bomb exploded in the 
Bekaa Valley town of Barr Elias. The blast set eight parked cars ablaze and 
damaged 12 stores. In a separate attack, a bomb exploded at a building in 
Muslim West Beirut near a Syrian army checkpoint, wounding six people, police 
said. There were no claims of responsibility for the blasts. 
</P>
