<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAUL IRWIN KAMIN; CIVIC LEADER, PHILANTHROPIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saul Irwin Kamin, 86, prominent civic leader and philanthropist in the Palm 
Springs area who presided over golf's Bob Hope Chrysler Classic in 1977 and 
1988. A one-time Pittsburgh car dealer who moved into the investment field, 
Kamin in retirement became a member of the Eisenhower Medical Center Board of 
Trustees. He also served the medical center as chairman of its development 
committee, member of the executive and financial committees and secretary of 
the Barbara Sinatra Children's Center. In Rancho Mirage on Monday of cancer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Obituary 
</P>
