<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 ACCIDENTS ON SAME SIMI STREET KILL MOTORCYCLIST, INJURE 7 OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Simi Valley street was the scene of two major accidents about 11 hours apart, 
one of which resulted in the death of a teen-age motorcyclist, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Daniel Armstrong, 17, of Simi Valley was struck and killed at 12:09 p.m. Friday 
as he was riding his motorcycle on Fitzgerald Road west of Mead Avenue. 
Armstrong, who was not wearing a helmet, hit a car driven by David Schmidt, 19, 
of Simi Valley, who was making a U-turn, Police Lt. Don Austin said. 
</P>
<P>
Schmidt suffered severe cuts to the face and hands, and Armstrong's companion 
on the motorcycle, Robert Molidor, suffered a broken leg and head injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Almost 11 hours later, five Simi Valley teen-agers were injured near the same 
spot on Fitzgerald when their driver lost control of the car, which hit a 
parked motor home and car, Austin said. 
</P>
<P>
Two passengers, Hugo Hernandez, 16, and Lisa Avendano, 15, were in critical 
condition from head injuries Saturday at Simi Valley Adventist Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Another passenger, Lori Duron, 15, was in satisfactory condition. The other two 
occupants, including the 15-year-old unlicensed driver, were treated and 
released from the hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
