MARINARO HELPS LAZERS TO A 4-3 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hector Marinaro scored 2 first-half goals Saturday to spark the Lazers to their 
sixth consecutive home victory, a 4-3 Major Indoor Soccer League victory over 
the Tacoma Stars at the Forum. 
</P>
<P>
The Lazers led at halftime, 4-1, and held off Tacoma to even their record at 
12-12. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Collins and Gary Heale each collected a goal and an assist for Los 
Angeles, which won despite being outshot in the second half, 27-4. 
</P>
<P>
Lazer rookie goalkeeper Kris Peate improved his record to 5-1. 
</P>
<P>
Preki had two goals -- his 26th and 27th of the season -- and an assist for the 
Stars. 
