</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dan Jansen of the United States won the 500-meter World Cup speed skating race 
and finished second to Uwe Jens Mey of East Germany in the 1,000-meter event at 
Miola di Pine, Italy. 
</P>
<P>
Jansen, 16th in the overall World Cup standings, covered the 500 meters in 
37.42 seconds to edge Ki Tae Bae of South Korea, who was timed in 36.45. Three 
Americans followed, with Nick Thometz fourth at 37.65, Eric Flaim fifth at 
38.04 and David Cruickhans sixth at 38.27. 
