</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Swedish rookie Catharina Glasser-Bjerner, 24, came from behind to win the giant 
slalom on the U.S. Women's Pro Ski Tour at Stowe, Vt. 
</P>
<P>
Glasser-Bjerner, the tour points leader, trailed Roswitha Raudaschl of Austria 
after the first heat of the finals, but made up the necessary time in the 
second run. 
</P>
<P>
Glasser-Bjerner has won giant slaloms this season at Park City, Utah, and 
Waterville Valley,N.H. 
