<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEFENDING CHAMPION LOPEZ'S 69 TIES DANIEL FOR LEAD IN FLORIDA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOCA RATON, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Defending champion Nancy Lopez shot a bogey-free 69 to overcome a 3-stroke 
deficit and tie Beth Daniel for the lead after three rounds of the Ladies 
Professional Golf Assn. Oldsmobile tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez birdied the 17th hole with a 12-foot putt to pull even with Daniel, who 
shot even-par 72 for a 54-hole total of 7-under-par 209 on the 6,333-yard 
Stonebridge Golf and Country Club course. 
</P>
<P>
A hole in one and 4 birdies helped Dottie Mochrie come from 6 strokes off the 
pace to gain a brief share of the lead. But the second-year pro, looking for 
her first tour victory, bogeyed No. 18 for a 67 to fall a shot behind Lopez and 
Daniel. 
</P>
<P>
Jane Geddes (69) and Jody Rosenthal (71) are next at 211. Lopez, with husband 
Ray Knight standing in for her regular caddy, birdied the first hole to move 
within 2 shots of Daniel. She also birdied No. 8 to take a share of the lead 
Daniel built by shooting 69 and 68 in the first 2 rounds. 
</P>
<P>
Mochrie, who earned $137,293 as a rookie last year, got her hole in one on the 
11th hole with a 3-iron that bounced twice and rolled into the cup 169 yards 
away. 
</P>
</TEXT>
