<P>
TITAN WOMEN TOP SAN DIEGO ST. IN BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kathy Werth hit a 12-foot jumper with a little more than 3 minutes remaining 
and Cal State Fullerton held on for a 57-56 upset of 14th-ranked San Diego 
State in a Big West women's basketball game Saturday night at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton (13-4 overall, 5-3 in conference play) took a 57-50 lead on Werth's 
jumper, but the Aztecs to make it a 1-point game. Trailing 57-56, San Diego 
inbounded the ball, but with 4 seconds remaining, Julie Evans' desperation shot 
from 15 feet was wide and Fullerton regained possession. 
</P>
<P>
Gena Miller scored a game-high 22 points and Werth added 17 for Fullerton. 
Chana Perry scored 17 for San Diego (16-3, 7-3). 
</P>
<P>
In another Big West women's game: 
</P>
<P>
