</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Preston hit 2 home runs and knocked in 3 runs for The Master's College, 
but host Cal State Los Angeles rallied for 2 runs in the ninth inning to defeat 
the Mustangs, 7-6, Saturday in a baseball opener. 
</P>
<P>
With Master's leading, 6-5, in the ninth, Mustang relief pitcher Ray Cartagena 
gave up 2 walks and Brad Mengel hit a run-scoring double for Cal State L. A. to 
tie the score. Mike Lau knocked in the winning run on a bad-hop single that 
bounced off the nose of Mustang second baseman Craig Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
Preston hit a 2-run home run in the first to lead a 4-run Master's rally and 
added a solo blast in the sixth. 
</P>
