<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL; 
</P>
<P>
CATALINA TRIP TWICE AS NICE FOR OAKWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It is unusual for a team to play the same league opponent 2 days in a row. And 
it's even more rare for a team to play both games on the other team's home 
court -- and win both. But that's exactly what Oakwood did Friday and Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Playing at Avalon High on Santa Catalina Island, Oakwood defeated the Lancers, 
59-52, Saturday in a Liberty League game. The victory followed a 71-53 win 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Mitchell Butler led the Gorillas to both victories, scoring 24 points and 
grabbing 14 rebounds Saturday to go along with 37 points, 11 rebounds, 6 
assists and 10 steals Friday. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. Baptist 31, Miraleste 28 -- Brett Craig, the Knights' leading scorer, was 
held to 5 points, but teammate Dave Garcia picked up the slack with 16 points 
in the nonleague game at L. A. Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
Garcia made 6 of 8 field-goal attempts as L. A. Baptist shot 60% (12 of 20) 
from the floor. 
</P>
<P>
Crossroads 56, Campbell Hall 54 (2 OTs) -- Ty Leatherman hit a 3-point shot for 
Campbell Hall to send the game into double overtime. Richard Strayer scored 16 
points for Campbell Hall and teammate Phil Bruno added 15 points and 10 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
Oakwood 43, Avalon 32 -- Capucine Rubin scored a game-high 20 points and pulled 
down 16 rebounds for Oakwood in the Liberty League game at Avalon as the 
Gorillas posted their eighth consecutive win. 
</P>
<P>
The Gorillas (11-2, 5-0) defeated Avalon, 43-30, on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. Baptist 56, Miraleste 21 -- Jill Shackelford scored 14 points and Kristin 
Heerema added 13 for the Knights in the nonleague game at L. A. Baptist. 
</P>
