<HEADLINE>
<P>
1 KILLED, 1 INJURED IN TRUCK CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A San Juan Capistrano man was killed and another person injured early Saturday 
when their pickup crashed on the Santa Ana Freeway at La Paz Road, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The Orange County coroner's office identified the dead driver as John Haynes, 
23. A California Highway Patrol dispatcher said that Haynes was heading south 
on the freeway at 2:30 a.m., going 80 to 85 m.p.h., when he lost control as he 
tried to change lanes. 
</P>
<P>
The truck veered across the highway and flipped, throwing Haynes onto the 
pavement, the dispatcher said. Haynes was not wearing his seat belt. The 
passenger, who was belted in, suffered a broken shoulder and was treated at 
Mission Community Hospital in Mission Viejo. 
</P>
<P>
The identity of the injured passenger was not released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
